   "source": [
    "Example:\n",
    "    \n",
    "Lets take an example of Blogging App - where we want to show the\n",
    "- user first name\n",
    "- user posts, that has ever created\n",
    "- display last 3 followers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### To Tackle above Screen using REST - API"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To Tackle above Screen using REST - API\n",
    "\n",
    "In Rest,we typically have 3 Endpoints:\n",
    "\n",
    "/users/<id>\n",
    "/users/<id>/posts\n",
    "/users/<id>/followers\n",
    "\n",
    "So, first we hit the endpoint : /users/<id> and server will respond with below information:\n",
    "{\n",
    "    \"users\":{\n",
    "        \"id\": 1,\n",
    "        \"name\": \"sumanshu\",\n",
    "        \"address\": {...},\n",
    "        \"birthday\": \"Jan 01 1990\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "As we need only 'Name' ; but we are also downloading the additional information; which is not relevant to this application. So this is not a desirable situation, but now atleast we have a user's name and we can display it on a profile screen.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next we need the POSTS, so we will use the /users/<id>/posts. This time server will return below details\n",
    "{\n",
    "    \"posts\": [\n",
    "        {\n",
    "         \"id\": 1,\n",
    "        \"title\": \"Post1\",\n",
    "        \"content\": \"Learn GraphQL Today....\",\n",
    "        \"comments\": [.....]\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        {\n",
    "         \"id\": 2,\n",
    "        \"title\": \"Post2\",\n",
    "        \"content\": \"Learn GraphQL with Python Today....\",\n",
    "        \"comments\": [.....]\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        {\n",
    "         \"id\": 3,\n",
    "        \"title\": \"Post3\",\n",
    "        \"content\": \"Learn GraphQL Implementation Today....\",\n",
    "        \"comments\": [.....]\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "Again, we are downloading a lot of additional information, thats not really relevant to that app. Because we only want the title of the post, but anyhow atleast now we have the title as well.\n",
    "\n",
    "And finally, for our last requirements - we will hit the /users/<id>/followers\n",
    "Again, we will send the GET request and again server response with a lot of information.\n",
    "\n",
    "{\n",
    "    \"followers\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"id\": 1,\n",
    "        \"name\": \"follower1\",\n",
    "        \"address\": {....},\n",
    "        \"birthday\": \"...\"\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"id\": 2,\n",
    "        \"name\": \"follower2\",\n",
    "        \"address\": {....},\n",
    "        \"birthday\": \"...\"\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"id\": 3,\n",
    "        \"name\": \"follower3\",\n",
    "        \"address\": {....},\n",
    "        \"birthday\": \"...\"\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "we only want to dislay the name, and we get so many information."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### So, How we can solve the situation with a GraphQL ?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With GraphQL - we only have a single Endpoint that can be used by all the different clients.\n",
    "that want to retrieve the data from the server.\n",
    "\n",
    "So with GraphQL, we only send a single request to the server and the server will return with all the information that you need.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will send the POST request to the server and in the body we will include the Query that describes all the data requirements.\n",
    "\n",
    "Client -------------HTTP POST-------> SERVER\n",
    "\n",
    "query {\n",
    "    User(id:1){\n",
    "    name\n",
    "    posts{\n",
    "    title\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    followers(last:3){\n",
    "    name\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "So we are asking for the user with a particular ID = 1; then we can specify what all the data we need of that user. When server recieve this query, it will process and resolve it to fetch exactly the data thats specified in the query and read it from the database.\n",
    "\n",
    "It will then package it up into a JSON object that it just returns to the client.\n",
    "The root field in the JSON object is called 'data'.\n",
    "\n",
    "Response will look as below:-\n",
    "\n",
    "{\n",
    "    \"data\": {\n",
    "        \"User\": {\n",
    "            \"name\": \"Sumanshu\",\n",
    "            \"posts\": [\n",
    "                {\"title\" : \"Title-1\"},\n",
    "                {\"title\" : \"Title-2\"},\n",
    "                {\"title\" : \"Title-3\"}\n",
    "            ],\n",
    "            \"followers\":[\n",
    "                {\"name\":\"follower-1\"},\n",
    "                {\"name\":\"follower-2\"},\n",
    "                {\"name\":\"follower-3\"}\n",
    "            ]\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# The other benefits of GraphQL over REST are :\n",
    "\n",
    "1 - No more over and under fetching,\n",
    "    Overfetching - downloading unncessary data.\n",
    "    Underferching - i.e. a Specific endpoint does not retun enough of the right information; thus need to send multiple request (like in REST).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "2 - Rapid Product Iterations.\n",
    "    in REST - we need to sructure endpoints based on client data needs. This does not allow rapid production. because there may be high risk with every change.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    with GraphQL - No need to adjust API when product requirements and design change. So faster product iterations.\n",
    "    \n",
    "3 - Insigtful analystics - We got to know what data is read by clients., what information they are interested in. So in future we can deprecate the fields which are not required by the clients."
   ]
  }
 ],
